The paper deals with building a navigational agent that can understand natural language instructions and act in the real-world environment, which falls under the domain of AI. The paper also involves language understanding and grounding, which is a subfield of computational linguistics (CL). The paper proposes a new training method that combines reinforcement learning and imitation learning, which is a common topic in machine learning (LG). The paper also involves perception of the scene, which is a topic in computer vision (CV). Finally, the paper deals with navigation in the real-world environment, which is a topic in robotics (RO). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.CV, and cs.RO.
